      "picks_file": "picks/picks-2026-05-23-1746.md",
      "why_text": "One day after The Late Show's final CBS broadcast, Stephen Colbert didn't disappear quietly \u2014 he resurfaced on a local Monroe, Michigan public access channel with an absurdist farewell special stacked with Jack White, Jeff Daniels, Eminem, Steve Buscemi, and Byron Allen. It's a deliberately lo-fi mic drop: after decades of prestige late night, Colbert chose public access as his final statement, which is both a joke and a genuine rebuke of the formats that define mainstream TV success. The stunt lands harder because it actually worked \u2014 the celebrity lineup made it a cultural event, not a gag.",
